## Phase 3: Multi-Language Translation (Enhanced)

Currently, the translation is hardcoded to Bengali via a prompt hack. The PRD requires support for Hindi, Bengali, Tamil, and other Indian languages with proper Sarvam Translation API calls.

### File Changes
| Action | File | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| NEW | `components/LanguageSelector.tsx` | Dropdown to pick language (Hindi, Bengali, Tamil, etc.) |
| MODIFY | [app/api/chat/route.ts](file:///d:/Ganesh/Office/Personal%20AI%20Agent/app/api/chat/route.ts) | Replace prompt-based translation with Sarvam's dedicated `/translate` API. Accept `language` param from frontend. |
| MODIFY | [app/page.tsx](file:///d:/Ganesh/Office/Personal%20AI%20Agent/app/page.tsx) | Add language selector to header. Pass selected language with each message. |

### Architecture Change
```
Current:  Bengali prompt hack → Sarvam LLM translates via system prompt
New:      Sarvam /translate API (Bengali→English) → Pinecone → Sarvam /translate API (English→Bengali)
```
Using the dedicated Translation API is faster and more accurate than asking the LLM to translate.

