## Phase 4: Voice Assistant (STT + TTS)

### New Dependencies
```bash
npm install @sarvam-ai/sdk  # If available, else use fetch() to hit Sarvam REST APIs directly
```

### File Changes
| Action | File | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| NEW | `app/api/stt/route.ts` | Accepts audio blob, calls Sarvam STT API, returns text |
| NEW | `app/api/tts/route.ts` | Accepts text string, calls Sarvam TTS API, returns audio |
| NEW | `components/VoiceButton.tsx` | Mic button with recording state, waveform animation |
| NEW | `hooks/useVoiceRecorder.ts` | Custom hook for `MediaRecorder` API |
| MODIFY | [app/page.tsx](file:///d:/Ganesh/Office/Personal%20AI%20Agent/app/page.tsx) | Add mic button next to send button. Add speaker icon on AI messages. |

### Data Flow (Voice Mode)
1. Engineer presses 🎤 → browser records audio via `MediaRecorder`
2. Audio blob sent to `POST /api/stt` → Sarvam STT returns text
3. Text auto-populates input → triggers normal chat pipeline
4. AI response text sent to `POST /api/tts` → Sarvam TTS returns audio
5. Browser plays audio via `<audio>` element or `AudioContext`

